==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* [[complete]]

===Verb===
'''compleat''' ([[compleats]], [[compleated]], [[compleating]])

# to [[finish]]; to make [[done]]; to reach the [[end]].
# to make [[whole]] or [[entire]].

====Translations====
See the compleat list at [[complete]].

===References===
*''He is at this time transporting large armies of foreign mercenaries to compleat the works of death, desolation and tyranny, already begun with circumstances of cruelty and perfidy unworthy the head of a civilized nation...'' -- 1776 [[CE]], the [[w:Declaration of Independence|Declaration of Independence]], written largely by [[w:Thomas Jefferson|Thomas Jefferson]].

===Adjective===
'''compleat'''

# with everything included; [[entire]], [[total]].
# [[quintessential]].

===References===
*''Here was the compleat modern misfit: the very air appeared to poison him;his every step looked treacherous and hard won [...] beneath an anarchy as much physiological as psychological.'' -- Stephen Schiff.

